Committee: Health and Human Services
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to the Health Care Facility Licensure Act; to
2 amend section 71-404, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024;
3 to redefine a term; to repeal the original section; and to declare
4 an emergency.
5 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1057 LB1057
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 71-404, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 71-404 (1) Adult day service means a person or any legal entity
4 which provides care and an array of social, medical, or other support
5 services for a period of less than twenty-four consecutive hours in a
6 community-based group program to four or more persons who require or
7 request such services due to age or functional impairment.
8 (2) Adult day service does not include community-based waiver
9 services provided by an entity certified as a specialized program
10 pursuant to under the Developmental Disabilities Services Act or a PACE
11 center.
12 Sec. 2. Original section 71-404, Revised Statutes Cumulative
13 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
14 Sec. 3. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
15 passed and approved according to law.
